{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Santa had a cup of coffee and he ate a little snack
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Throwed his old pack right over his back
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Opened the window of his little
[D7]And shouted oh Dasher and [G7]Dancer
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]Vixen and Blitzen come on here
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
We’re gonna get a-goin' and spread some cheer
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
So limber your legs and sharpen your hooves
[G7]Cause tonight is the night we’re gonna jump on the [C]roof
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[F]So the reindeer they were so proud and grand
[C]To take another trip all over the land
[G7]They jumped right into their proper place
[C]To get hepped up for that [G7]midnight [C]race
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
Ol' Santa he shook off the ice and snow
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
Boarded his sleigh and then yelled let's go
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
All the little toys were happy too
[D7]Because they were so bright and [G7]new
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 11}
[C]A little piano then started to play
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 12}
Ol' Santa began to swing and to sway
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 13}
Thought he heard a toy drum starting to beat
[G7]But he found it was the rhythm of the reindeer’s [C]feet
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 14}
[F]The reindeer boogied in the middle of the road
[C]Tonight we have a mighty big load
[G7]Don't boogie to the left now boogie to the right
[C]Do the reindeer boogie this [G7]Christmas Eve [C]night
{end_of_verse}

